Paratetilla bacca
has a wide distribution in Indonesia, including Berau, Bunaken, Raja Ampat, 
Ternate
, and Java. Previous Indonesian records are from Spermonde Archipelago (
Becking et al. 2006
), Berau (
de Voogd et al. 2009
), and Raja Ampat (
Becking 2008
). In addition, this species has also been reported from Seychelles Islands (
Thomas 1973
), Southwest Madagascar (
Vacelet et al. 1976
), Zanzibar (
Pulitzer-Finali 1993
), Thailand (
Putchakarn 2007
), Singapore (
Lim et al. 2008
), Philippines (
Longakit et al. 2005
) (Figure 2).
